{{notability|1=Biographies|date=March 2018}} {{infobox person | name = Evan Eckenrode | image = Evan Eckenrode.jpg | imagesize = 250px | caption = Picture of Eckenrode in 2018 | birth_name = Evan Eckenrode | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1997|02|11}} | birth_place = [[Smithsburg, Maryland]], U.S. | residence = [[Los Angeles]], [[California]], U.S. | alias = Dwarf Mamba | alma_mater = [[Salisbury University]] | occupation = {{flatlist| *Actor *comedian *Vine celebrity *filmmaker *internet personality}} | years_active = 2010–present }}
'''Evan Eckenrode''' (born February 11, 1997) is an American [[comedian]], [[filmmaker]], [[internet personality]] and former [[Vine (service)|Vine]] star. Eckenrode is best known for his work on [[Vine (service)|Vine]], and on the video platform [[YouTube]]. His other projects included collaborations with his roommate [[Logan Paul]].
Eckenrode began filming [[Vine (service)|Vine]] videos in his hometown of [[Smithsburg, Maryland]] with his high school friends, most of which lightheartedly emphasized his dwarfism. By the time [[Vine]] shutdown, Eckenrode amassed a following of over two millions viewers. His YouTube account, DwarfMamba, recently achieved the same number of subscribers.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://socialblade.com/youtube/channel/UC1bMs87K1YPMcs8Wb5L0ndw/realtime |title=Real Time YouTube Subscriber Count |author=SocialBlade |publisher=SocialBlade |accessdate=February 27, 2018|date=September 12, 2018}}</ref>
He later attended [[Salisbury University]] for a degree in business, but soon left to pursue his career on social media from the urging of Paul.
