{{about|the Dutch politician|the English singer|Kathleen Ferrier}}
{{Infobox Politician | name = Kathleen Ferrier | image = 2010-12-19 piment ferrier.JPG | office = [[House of Representatives of the Netherlands|Member of the House of Representatives (Netherlands)]] | term_start = May 23, 2002 | term_end = September 19, 2012 | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1957|3|8|mf=y}} | birth_place = [[Paramaribo]], [[Suriname (Kingdom of the Netherlands)|Suriname]] | birthname = Kathleen Gertrud Ferrier | nationality = [[Netherlands|Dutch]] | party = [[Christian Democratic Appeal]] (Christen-Democratisch Appèl - CDA) | spouse = Tjeerd de Boer | residence = [[Leusden]], Netherlands | alma_mater = [[Leiden University]] | education = [[Master of Arts|M.A.]] ([[Spanish language]] and [[Spanish literature|literature]], [[Portuguese language]] and [[Development aid]]) | occupation = Politician, development aid worker | religion = [[Protestant Church in the Netherlands]] | signature = | website = | father = [[Johan Ferrier]] }}
'''Kathleen Gertrud Ferrier''' (born March 8, 1957) is a former [[Netherlands|Dutch]] politician of [[Surinamese people|Surinamese]] descent and [[development aid]] worker. She served as a member of parliament of Netherlands representing the party [[Christian Democratic Appeal]] (Christen-Democratisch Appèl) from 2002 to 2012.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.parlement.com/id/vg9fgoprwbx2/k_g_kathleen_ferrier|title=Drs. K.G. (Kathleen) Ferrier|accessdate=June 13, 2017|publisher=Parlement and Politiek|language=nl}}</ref>
==Early life and education== Ferrier was born in [[Paramaribo]] in [[Suriname]] when it was a constituent country of the [[Kingdom of the Netherlands]]. She is a daughter of the first President of Suriname [[Johan Ferrier]]<ref name=star>{{cite news|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/next-step/face-off/from-professorship-to-politics-1417402|author=Raisa Ashraf|title=From professorship to politics|date=June 9, 2017|accessdate=June 13, 2017|newspaper=The Daily Star}}</ref> and a half-sister of Surinamese novelist [[Cynthia McLeod]]. Ferrier studied [[Spanish language]] and [[Spanish literature]] (with a specialization in modern [[Latin American literature|Spanish American literature]]), [[Portuguese language]] and also development aid at [[Leiden University]]. She completed her masters' thesis on the Cuban poet [[Nicolás Guillén]].<ref name=star/>
She is a member of the [[Protestant Church in the Netherlands]] (PKN).
==Career== While Ferrier was an MP from May 23, 2002, to September 19, 2012, she focused on matters of development aid, education, [[public health]], welfare and sports. In 2017, Ferrier joined [[Asian University for Women]] (AUW) as an honorary visiting professor.<ref name=star/>
== Decorations == * Knight of the [[Order of Orange-Nassau]] (2012).
